<br>
On the left isle after you have killed the raptor stated above, there is a raptor that is on the beach near the water... tactic ive used is to keep levitate up, and use a staff of warding for the zoom effect.  stay near the shore and inch up to it until you see that it aggros... run back to your pet (which should now be guarding on the spot you killed the 1st raptor), kill that raptor... now it's up to you.. if you want to stay at 2 raptors per spawn, just rest med up and have pet sitdown to recover htpts faster.  If you want to do a 3rd raptor, the one ive done is the raptor behind the hut on the 2nd island.  use the same tactic above with the staff of warding and you can pull him as well... just im my situation i usually ended up with about 20m pet at 30% health, and the 1st raptor to respawn in about 5-6 mins... enough time for 2-3 bubs of mana... so you can alternate between doing 2 and 3 spawns per cycle... i went thru 54 fairly quickly doing just those 3 spawns.<br>
<br>
Raptors are pretty good exp up to about 58, so you can do those 3 spawns, or grab a druid and AE kite 4-6 at a time, which really makes the exp fly, if you intend to do this, pull them to the chessboard island where you have some room to manuever... it's great exp.<br>
<br>
<br>
Laelaran Fyrestaff<br>
55th Conjurer<br>
The Companions<br>
